      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 210,
      "message": "I kept looking at this and thinking there must be a better way to do this.  Finally figured out this could have been done using set operations, eliminating the middle loop.  Instead of looping through the values, just create a set that's a copy of entry1.getValue() and then removeAll(entry2.getValue()).  If the result is non-empty, then you know there's overlap.\n\nNevertheless, it's okay the way it's written.  Maybe next time.",
      "author": {
